red perch
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Alternative name for the butterfly perch; brightly and variably coloured; common around northern NZ.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: butterfly perch
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Caesioperca lepidoptera</i> aka butterfly perch, red snapper, St. Peter's Fish, or bastard long-fin'
